{'book': {'publisher': 'Avon a', 'synopsis': 'In this groundbreaking companion to The Courage to Heal, Laura Davis offers an inspiring, in-depth workbook that speaks to all women and men healing from the effects of child sexual abuse. The combination of checklists, writing and art Projects, open-ended questions and activities expertly guides the survivor through the healing process. Survival Skills—Teaches survivors to create a safe, supportive environment, ask for help, deal with crisis periods, and choose therapy. Aspects Of Healing—Focuses on the healing process: gaining a capacity for hope, breaking silence, letting go of shame, turning anger into action, planning a confrontation, preparing for family contact, and affirming personal progress. Guidelines For Healing Sexually—Redefines the concept of "safe sex" and establishes healthy ground rules for sexual contact.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/43/75/9780060964375.jpg', 'title_long': 'The Courage to Heal Workbook', 'edition': '1', 'dimensions': 'Weight: 0.78 Pounds', 'dimensions_structured': {'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.78}}, 'pages': 480, 'date_published': '1990', 'subjects': ['Parenting & Relationships'], 'authors': ['Laura Davis'], 'title': 'The Courage to Heal Workbook', 'isbn13': '9780060964375', 'msrp': 12.81, 'binding': 'Paperback', 'isbn': '0060964375', 'isbn10': '0060964375'}}